Package org.iot.dsa.dslink

DSLink is the main entry point for an application.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DSLinkSession
    Represents a line of communication with a remote entity.
    DSRequester
    Session object used by requesters.
    DSRequesterInterface  
    DSResponder
    Interface for nodes in the node tree to manually handle requests.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DSLink
    Represents an upstream connection, a node hierarchy, and manages the lifecycle of both.
    DSLinkConfig
    Configuration options for starting a link.
    DSLinkConnection
    Represents an upstream connection with a broker.
    DSRootNode
    A DSNode and DSResponder that converts the node model into DSA.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DSInvalidPathException
    Indicates a request path was invalid.
    DSPermissionException
    Indicates a request has insufficient permissions.
    DSRequestException
    Indicates something was wrong with a request.
